al name from Lorraine, a region in the northeastern part of France. Its name derives from the name of the medieval kingdom of Lotharingia, which in turn was named for its sovereign <i>Lothar</i> (a personal name composed of the elements <i>hlūd</i> ‘famous, renowned’ + <i>hari</i>, <i>heri</i> ‘army’).","Altered form of French   Lorrain  , a variant of 1 above."],"variants":[{"name":"Loring","meanings":["English: ethnic name from Old French <i>Lohereng</i> ‘man fromLorraine’ (see   Lorraine  )."]},{"name":"Lorrain","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Adrien, Alban, Andre, Desire, Fernande, Philippe, Pierre.","French: variant of   Lorraine  . This surname is also found in Britain. Compare   Laurain   and   Laurin  .","History: Pierre Lorrain <i>dit</i> Lachapelle from Angliers in Vienne, France, married Françoise Hulin in France <i>c.</i> 1656."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Ermesinde de Lorraine was born on 24 February 1033, in Longwy, Meurthe-et-Moselle, Lorraine, France. She had at least 2 daughters with Pierre-Guillaume d'Aquitaine VII. She died in 1068, in Roma, Lazio, Italy, at the age of 35."},"et":{"24 February 1033–1068":"24. veebruar 1033–1068","1023–1058":"1023–1058","1052–1089":"1052–1089","1060–1142":"1060–1142","1033–1068":"1033–1068","1058":"1058","1068":"1068","1089":"1089","1023":"1023","about 1058":"umbes 1058","1033":"1033","24 February 1033":"24. veebruar 1033","1142":"1142","1030":"1030","1052":"1052","1060":"1060","Rome, Lazio, Italy":"Roma, Lazio, Itaalia","Poitou, Charentes, Duché d'Aquitaine":"Charente, Nouvelle-Aquitaine, Prantsusmaa","Poitiers, Vienne, Poitou-Charentes, France":"Poitiers, Vienne, Poitou-Charentes, Prantsusmaa","Longwy, Meurthe-et-Moselle, Lorraine, France":"Longwy, Meurthe-et-Moselle, Lorraine, Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"24 February 1033–1068":"24. helmikuuta 1033–1068","1023–1058":"1023–1058","1052–1089":"1052–1089","1060–1142":"1060–1142","1033–1068":"1033–1068","1058":"1058","1068":"1068","1089":"1089","1023":"1023","abo